						               													<description>From the Publishers website:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The War in the Western Desert of Egypt is the focus of the &amp;lsquo;Desert Rats&amp;rsquo; of the British Army and its Imperial allies as the third year of the war draws to a close. Here they fight General Rommel, the legendary &amp;lsquo;Desert Fox&amp;rsquo; and his Afrika Korps and Italian allies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As this heroic struggle plays out, the US Army enters the fray for the first time, landing in Algeria and Morocco behind Rommel&amp;rsquo;s forces. Trapped between two foes the Desert Fox does the only thing possible, he attacks!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This book enables you to recreate the famous battles of El Alamein, Kasserine pass, Sicily and Salerno with the Flames Of War the World War II Miniatures Game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INSIDE YOU WILL FIND:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Complete organization and equipment for all the forces in the Mediterranean Theater, 1942-43.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; An overall history of what happened in the theater, as well as individual histories of the nations involved.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Guides to German, Italian, British and US Divisions in North Africa, Sicily and Italy.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Inspiring color photos.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Comprehensive painting guides.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Airborne assault mission to use with your German and US paratroops.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Exploits of inspirational historic figures such as Captain Charles Upham, Technical Sergeant &amp;lsquo;Commando&amp;rsquo; Kelly, Tenente Luigi Pascucci and Generalfeldmarschall Erwin Rommel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flames of War current rulebook range&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
